<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5536] ConfigSpiOSGi may end with incomplete realm due to race conditions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5536</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some race conditions around this have been fixed with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5505&quot; title=&quot;ConfigSpiOSGi may miss out on registering some LoginModuleFactory due to race condition&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FELIX-5505&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FELIX-5505&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. However one more case surfaced where &lt;tt&gt;ConfigSpiOsgi#recreateConfigs&lt;/tt&gt; can be invoked concurrently without lock from &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ConfigSpiOsgi#updated&lt;/tt&gt; - When ConfigurationAdmin dispatches config update for &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.felix.jaas.ConfigurationSpi&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ConfigSpiOsgi#addingService&lt;/tt&gt; - When some LoginModuleFactory is registered&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In such a case the setup may end up with incomplete realm where some LoginModuleFactory are missed out&lt;/p&gt;</description>
